## Design Philosophy

### Core Principles

**1. Developer-First Aesthetic**
- Dark mode optimized for extended coding sessions
- High contrast for code readability
- Subtle, professional color palette
- Minimal visual noise

**2. Visual Hierarchy**
- Clear information architecture
- Consistent spacing patterns
- Strategic use of color and contrast
- Purposeful animations

**3. Performance & Accessibility**
- Fast rendering with minimal reflows
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility

---

## Color System

### Design Tokens

Our color system uses **OKLCH color space** for perceptually uniform colors and better dark mode support.

#### Primary Colors

\`\`\`css
--primary: oklch(0.65 0.25 265)        /* Electric purple/blue */
--primary-foreground: oklch(0.98 0 0)  /* Near white */
\`\`\`

**Usage:** Primary actions, focus states, active elements, key CTAs

#### Semantic Colors

\`\`\`css
/* Surface Colors */
--background: oklch(0.12 0 0)          /* Rich black canvas */
--card: oklch(0.16 0 0)                /* Elevated surfaces */
--popover: oklch(0.14 0 0)             /* Floating elements */
--secondary: oklch(0.22 0 0)           /* Subtle elevation */
--muted: oklch(0.22 0 0)               /* Disabled states */

/* Text Colors */
--foreground: oklch(0.95 0 0)          /* Primary text */
--muted-foreground: oklch(0.55 0 0)    /* Secondary text */
--secondary-foreground: oklch(0.95 0 0)

/* Functional Colors */
--destructive: oklch(0.55 0.22 25)     /* Error/delete states */
--border: oklch(0.25 0 0)              /* Dividers & borders */
--input: oklch(0.25 0 0)               /* Form inputs */
--ring: oklch(0.65 0.25 265)           /* Focus rings */
\`\`\`

#### Chart & Visualization Colors

\`\`\`css
--chart-1: oklch(0.65 0.25 265)        /* Primary purple */
--chart-2: oklch(0.6 0.2 200)          /* Cyan blue */
--chart-3: oklch(0.7 0.18 150)         /* Mint green */
--chart-4: oklch(0.75 0.2 80)          /* Warm yellow */
--chart-5: oklch(0.68 0.22 320)        /* Magenta pink */
\`\`\`

**Usage:** Data visualization, node type differentiation, status indicators

### Node Type Color Mapping

| Node Type | Color Token | Hex Equivalent | Usage |
|-----------|-------------|----------------|-------|
| Start | `bg-green-500` | `#22c55e` | Entry points |
| Text Model | `bg-primary` | `oklch(0.65 0.25 265)` | AI text generation |
| Image Gen | `bg-chart-1` | `oklch(0.65 0.25 265)` | AI image models |
| HTTP Request | `bg-blue-500` | `#3b82f6` | API integrations |
| Conditional | `bg-purple-500` | `#a855f7` | Logic branching |
| JavaScript | `bg-yellow-500` | `#eab308` | Custom code |
| Embedding | `bg-chart-2` | `oklch(0.6 0.2 200)` | Vector operations |
| Tool | `bg-chart-4` | `oklch(0.75 0.2 80)` | Function tools |
| Prompt | `bg-chart-5` | `oklch(0.68 0.22 320)` | Input prompts |
| End | `bg-red-500` | `#ef4444` | Output nodes |

### Color Usage Guidelines

**DO:**
- Use semantic tokens for UI elements (`bg-card`, `text-foreground`)
- Use chart colors for data visualization and node differentiation
- Maintain consistent hover states with 20% opacity overlays
- Use `border-2` for selected states

**DON'T:**
- Hardcode color values (use design tokens)
- Mix color systems (stick to OKLCH)
- Use more than 5 colors in a single visualization
- Override node type colors

